://github.com/glfw/glfw/blob/master/src/win32_window.c#L773)\n\nthis in my case resolve the failure.\nbut it is really thread safe?\n\n``` c++\n    if (!GetClassInfoW(GetModuleHandleW(NULL), _GLFW_WNDCLASSNAME, &wc))\n    {\n        if (!RegisterClassW(&wc))\n        {\n            _glfwInputError(GLFW_PLATFORM_ERROR,\n                \"Win32: Failed to register window class\");\n            return GL_FALSE;\n        }\n    }\n```\n\nor you can replace all\n[win32_window.c#L694](https://github.com/glfw/glfw/blob/master/src/win32_window.c#L694) [win32_window.c#L759](https://github.com/glfw/glfw/blob/master/src/win32_window.c#L759) [win32_window.c#L766](https://github.com/glfw/glfw/blob/master/src/win32_window.c#L766) [win32_window.c#L787](https://github.com/glfw/glfw/blob/master/src/win32_window.c#L787) \n\n``` c++\nGetModuleHandleW(NULL)\n```\n\n with:\n\n``` c++\nEXTERN_C IMAGE_DOS_HEADER __ImageBase;\n#define HINST_THISCOMPONENT ((HINSTANCE)&__ImageBase)\n ...\nwc.hInstance = HINST_THISCOMPONENT; // replace > GetModuleHandleW(NULL)\n...\n```\n\nthis ensure to use the right module hInstances, so we can have same named class, without clash.\n\nand it would also be preferable to give the opportunity to the user to name the windows class.\n","closed_by":{"login":"elmindreda","id":133714,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzMzcxNA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/133714?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda","html_url":"https://github.com/elmindreda","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmindreda/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elmi